                <header class="article-header">
                    <h1 itemprop="name"><a class="article-title" href="/post/26-05-23-tempophot/">Quick Repair: Tempophot</a></h1>
                </header>
                
                <div class="article-meta">
                    <a href="/post/26-05-23-tempophot/" class="article-date">
                        <time datetime='2023-05-26T09:35:41.000&#43;02:00' itemprop="datePublished">2023-05-26</time>
                    </a>
                    
                    
                    
                </div>
                <div class="article-entry" itemprop="articleBody">
                    <p>
                        <a class="article-title" href="/post/26-05-23-tempophot/"><img width=1000 height=100 alt="Banner" src="/post/26-05-23-tempophot//banner.jpg"></a><br>
                    
I got this old camera photometer a while back and it wasn&rsquo;t working, so I figured let&rsquo;s see what&rsquo;s wrong with it. Turns out the photocoll just wasn&rsquo;t making good contact, I rotated it slightly ~45° and the meter started working again.
The fotocell is dated 26. March 1935.
Links Tempophot - Antique and Vintage Cameras Tempophot T-4 
                    </p>
                    <p class="article-more-link">
                        <a href="/post/26-05-23-tempophot/">Read More</a>
                    </p>
                </div>

                
